# a.lower.sdd

Scope: Latin lowercase a prototype glyph.

## Must

- Provide the first high-personality lowercase glyph.
- Decide, or explicitly defer, single-storey versus double-storey construction.
- Test bowl, terminal, aperture, and counter logic against n and o.
- Make clear which parts are family logic and which parts are glyph-specific character.
- Keep this glyph as part of the `adhesion` prototype set.

## Must not

- Become decorative before the core rhythm is stable.
- Contradict o-counter logic without an explicit exception.

## Owns

- Lowercase personality test.
- Aperture and terminal behavior.
- Relationship between bowl logic and family round forms.
- Primary lower-round entry rhythm for the `adhesion` set.

## Depends on

- `n.lower.sdd`
- `o.lower.sdd`
- `../../design-principles.sdd`
- `../../metrics/spacing.sdd`

## Forbids

- Choosing single-storey/double-storey by generator convenience.

## Done when

- a works in `aaa`, `nan`, `ana`, `non`, `noa`, and `Maya` test strings once M/y exist.
- a is judged compatible with `adhesion` rhythm (`ad`, `da`, `na`, `oa`) before any phase expansion.
- Human review accepts its personality as compatible with the family direction.

## Proof-Control Note

- This spec is maintained as an `adhesion` control and phase-1 proof point.
- It also participates in legacy cross-checks with uppercase/legacy controls (`H/O/n/o`) while the project direction remains anchored to the `adhesion` set.
- Primary design-DNA set is `adhesion` (`a d h e s i o n`).